Jenna Etheridge, News24File, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A gang of armed robbers targeted a cash-in-transit van at a Cape Town business premises in broad daylight on Monday morning.Six unidentified men approached three security officers who were collecting cash boxes in Sunningdale around 08:20, said Western Cape police spokesperson Captain FC van Wyk.They hit one of the officers over the head with a handgun.The group then grabbed a cash box with an undisclosed amount of money. They fled the scene in a white Toyota Camry.It is understood that the van was parked at a petrol station next to the West Coast Village shopping centre.Van Wyk said the vehicle was later found abandoned in a nearby road.&nbsp;He said a witness saw the men jumping into a red Astra sedan.No shots were fired during the incident and the group was still on the run. Van Wyk said.An armed robbery case was being investigated. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.